Race = read-modify-write across two round trips (`SELECT` counter → `+1` in JS → `UPDATE`). Concurrent requests read the same value, both write the same increment. Fix: make the increment atomic in one SQL statement so Postgres serializes it.

```js
const { rows } = await pool.query(
  'UPDATE counters SET value = value + 1 WHERE id = $1 RETURNING value',
  [id]
);
const value = rows[0].value;
```

`value = value + 1` reads and writes under a row lock in a single statement — concurrent updates queue, each sees a distinct result. `RETURNING` hands back the post-increment value, so no separate `SELECT`.

